<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA General Task//EN" "generalTask.dtd">
<task id="t-icecreambase">
    <title>How to Make the Ice Cream Base</title>
    <shortdesc id="baseinfo">The base is stored in the Shanks' break room fridge and is replenished as necessary.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <p> Makes one gallon of ice cream base</p>
        <prereq>Ingredients: <ul>
                <li>8 cups half-n-half</li>
                <li>2 2/3 cups heav cream</li>
                <li>21 large egg yolks</li>
                <li>24 oz. (by weight) granulated sugar</li>
                <li>5 1/3 tsp. vanilla exract</li>
        </ul>
        </prereq>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Place sauce pan on stove over medium heat. Add the half-n-half and heavy cream. Bring to a simmer. Remove from heat.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Separate eggs and place the yolks into the mixing bowl. Whisk until color lightens.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Add the sugar and whisk to combine.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Temper the cream by adding the egg-sugar mixture in instalments, stirring to combine.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Return to low heat, stirring frequently until thick and the mixture reaches 170-175Ëš F </cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Pour mixture into a container and let sit for 30 mins. Add the vanilla extract.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Cover mixture and place in refridgerator.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
